Summary
-------

**Python**: >=3.8

`Project documentation <https://kaiju-redis.readthedocs.io/en/latest/>`_

Redis / keydb services (cache, streams, locks).

Use `pip install kaiju-redis` to install the package.

For development run the init script `tools/init.sh`.
It will setup git hooks and install the dev version of the project.

Testing
_______

- Install additional dependencies `pip install -e .[test]`
- Start docker daemon.
- Run `pytest` from the project root.

Documentation
_____________

Run `docs/docs.sh` from the project root to generate documentation.
